      "writtenOn": "2020-12-09T02:09:12Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I found that this is racy and doesn\u0027t guarantee cancelling incomplete steps always.\n\n(1) Build-A started.\n(2) At the same time,\n- Client-A updated Build-A with incomplete steps.\n- Client-B called UpdateBuild() for Build-A with\nMask: \"build.status\", \"build.status\"\nStatus: Status_SUCCESS\nSteps: complete-step\n \n(3) Client-A\u0027s request processed before Client-B\u0027s request.\n(4) Then, when Client-B\u0027s request is processed, L359 wouldn\u0027t scan the existing steps to cancel.\n\nThis won\u0027t happen if there is only one recipe handling the same Build, and it\u0027s probably true due to build_token? Let me know it\u0027s worth fetching BuildSteps always to find incomplete steps, whether the request has \"steps\" or not.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 360,
        "startChar": 4,
        "endLine": 360,
        "endChar": 11
      },
      "revId": "90511c27d094b91e135ee900655ff8d21964095a",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "d2d248c9_26f6d7dd",
        "filename": "buildbucket/appengine/rpc/update_build.go",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 360,
      "author": {
        "id": 1147264
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-12-09T02:12:58Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Thinking back, it doesn\u0027t have to be made by two clients.\nA single recipe can produce the same error.\n\n(1) Schedule Build.\n(2) Update the Build with incomplete step-A\n(3) Update the Build with Status_SUCCESS\nwith complete step-B, but w/o step-A.\n\nI will update this CL to scan and cancel the existing, incomplete steps always.",
      "parentUuid": "9f08306c_5328cce7",
